phase2.explanation:
HashSet uses equals() and hashCode() to determine if objects are duplicates.

Without overriding them, HashSet uses Object's default equals() (reference equality).

Two different objects with the same data are considered DIFFERENT.

FIX: Override equals() and hashCode():

@Override
public boolean equals(Object o) {
    if (this == o) return true;
    if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;
    Person person = (Person) o;
    return age == person.age && Objects.equals(name, person.name);
}

@Override
public int hashCode() {
    return Objects.hash(name, age);
}

Always override both when using custom objects in Sets!

